Interface AbstractThrowingConsumerN<H extends AbstractThrowingConsumerN.Handler,C extends AbstractThrowingConsumerN<H,C>>

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ThrowingConsumerN.Instance

    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractThrowingConsumerN<H extends AbstractThrowingConsumerN.Handler,C extends AbstractThrowingConsumerN<H,C>>
extends AbstractThrowingFunctionN<java.lang.Void,H>, net.ashwork.functionality.consumer.partial.ConsumerChainableConsumer<C>
    Represents an operation that accepts n arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable. All throwing consumers are derived from this n-arity specialization. This is the non-producing specialization of AbstractThrowingFunctionN. This is the throwing variation of AbstractConsumerN.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractThrowingFunctionN, AbstractConsumerN
    API Note:
    This is an abstract consumer and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
